narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course exposes students to visiting faculty in a seminar setting. Visiting faculty present topics pertinent to their research, allowing for questions and discussion.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
We were not informed when any of the seminars are taking place. In the first two weeks at the start of the semester a couple of first years and me went to Mason only to find an empty room, since then we thought the seminars are not taking place. Only in the last week in conversation with one professor we found out that some seminars took place.

We receive newsletters from other engineering departments regarding their seminars, but not our own.

Feedback for the whole academic year: During the first few weeks in Fall, we did not know what this course entailed and showed up several times, only finding an empty room. Later, we received information about when the seminars were happening, but this information stopped coming after winter break, so we thought it was not happening.
It is nice to hear the cutting edge of the industry.
This course (as offered in the spring) was difficult to get a schedule for, as it is run on a non-standard schedule.
